ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  I have made this joke before</a=
>, but events keep sharpening it. The OpenAI board looked at Sam Altman and=
 thought =E2=80=9Cthis guy is smarter than us, he can outmaneuver us in a p=
inch, and it makes us nervous.=C2=A0He=E2=80=99s done nothing wrong so far,=
 but we can=E2=80=99t be sure what he=E2=80=99ll do next as his capabilitie=
s expand.=C2=A0We do not fully trust him, we cannot fully control him, and =
we do not have a model of how his mind works that we fully understand. Ther=
efore we have to shut him down before he grows too powerful.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I=E2=80=99m sorry! That is exactly the AI misa=
lignment worry! If you spend your time managing AIs that are growing expone=
ntially smarter, you might worry about losing control of them, and if you s=
pend your time managing Sam Altman you might worry about losing control of =
him, and if you spend your time managing both of them you might get confuse=
