=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">I think that</a> the Ope=
nAI board two weeks ago (1) did not include any investor representatives an=
d (2) was=C2=A0<em>fundamentally unpredictable to investors=C2=A0</em>=E2=
=80=94 it might have gone and fired Altman! =E2=80=94=C2=A0whereas the futu=
re OpenAI board (1) will not include any investor representatives but (2) w=
ill nonetheless be a bit more constrained by the investors=E2=80=99 interes=
ts. =E2=80=9CIf we are=C2=A0<em>too=C2=A0</em>nonprofit-y, the company will=
 vanish in a puff of smoke, and that will be bad,=E2=80=9D the new board wi=
ll think, whereas the old board actually went around saying things like =E2=
=80=9Callowing the company to be destroyed would be consistent with the mis=
sion=E2=80=9D and almost meant it.=C2=A0The investors don=E2=80=99t exactly=
 need a board seat if they have a practical veto over the board=E2=80=99s b=
iggest decisions, and the events of the last two weeks suggest that they do=
.</p>
