 like this.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But there are other scandals that are a bit di=
fferent. Some scandals are caused by the facts that (1) the bank wants to m=
ake money, (2) it sets goals for employees that are=C2=A0<em>correlated=C2=
=A0</em>with making money, but that are not actually identical with =E2=80=
=9Cmake a lot of money,=E2=80=9D (3) the employees have incentives to meet =
those goals and are pressured to perform and (4) there are easy, degenerate=
 ways to meet those goals=C2=A0<em>without </em>making money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Most infamously, Wells Fargo &amp; Co. thought=
 to itself =E2=80=9Cif we cross-sell our customers on having lots of differ=
