. And the bankers realized that it was hard to sell customers extra product=
s, but relatively easy to, for instance, sign customers up for online banki=
ng or a credit card or a checking account without their permission. And so =
Wells Fargo <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/335238=
03.281430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTYtM=
