<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or, US law tries to discourage discriminatory =
lending decisions by banks by, among other things, asking banks to collect =
demographic data about their mortgage applicants. The bank asks customers t=
heir race and gender, it writes down the answers, it reports them to the go=
vernment, and if the government notices that the bank rejects 100% of Black=
 applicants then it can do something about it. This is a somewhat intrusive=
 thing to ask the customers, and they don=E2=80=99t have to answer: The cus=
tomer can just say =E2=80=9Cno thanks=E2=80=9D and the bank can report =E2=
=80=9Cdeclined to answer=E2=80=9D to the government.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You can see the easy, degenerate way to check =
that box. Here is a US Consumer Financial Protection Bureau <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33523803.281430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
